      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"adaptation_kind\":\"Restructure\",\"safety_tier\":\"Green\",\"nudge_patch\":null,\"restructure_plan\":{\"revised_weekly_targets\":[{\"week_number\":1,\"weekly_target_km\":48},{\"week_number\":2,\"weekly_target_km\":52},{\"week_number\":3,\"weekly_target_km\":57}],\"revised_current_week_workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":2,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":60,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start slowly. Let the body settle in.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":50,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady easy effort. Conversational pace throughout.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Wind down to a walk.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes easy jogging before settling into pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with 5 minutes of easy walking and light stretching.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run stays fully aerobic. If legs still feel flat, slow down further. There is no pace floor today.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"title\":\"Reduced Threshold Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":50,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":280,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog to prime the aerobic system before threshold work.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":30,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":280,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Continuous threshold effort. If pace slips significantly, back off to easy and cut the segment short rather than grinding.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog to flush the legs.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"10 minutes easy before the threshold block.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"10 minutes easy jog followed by walking.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Volume is trimmed from 12 km to 10 km. The threshold block is shortened to 30 minutes. If pace cannot hold near 280 s/km, convert the remaining time to easy running and note it in the log. The data from this run will inform next week.\",\"perceived_effort\":6},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"workout_type\":\"Interval\",\"title\":\"Short Interval Session\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":55,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":250,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog. Include 4 short 20-second strides at the end to prime the legs.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":20,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":250,\"intensity\":\"VO2Max\",\"repetitions\":4,\"notes\":\"4 reps instead of 6. Full recovery between each rep. Stop the session if pace cannot hold within the VO2Max zone. Quality over completion.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":12,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":4,\"notes\":\"Walk or very easy jog between intervals. Full recovery before the next rep.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog to close out.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"10 minutes easy with 4 strides at the end.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"10 minutes easy jog followed by stretching.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Session is rebuilt from 6 reps to 4. The goal is to complete all 4 at target pace, not to accumulate volume. If rep 3 or 4 slips badly, shut it down and log it. That information is useful.\",\"perceived_effort\":7},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Easy Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":18,\"target_duration_minutes\":107,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start conservatively. No rushing into pace.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":97,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady aerobic effort throughout. This is a time-on-feet run, not a pace run.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Walk the final few minutes.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes very easy before settling into long run pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with walking and full stretching routine.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Distance is pulled back from 22 km to 18 km. The pace stays fully aerobic at 360 s/km. Completing 18 km cleanly at easy effort is more useful than grinding through 22 km when the body is not responding.\",\"perceived_effort\":5}],\"forward_path\":\"Week 2 targets 52 km, a step up of 4 km from the revised Week 1. The long run rebuilds to 20 km, and the interval session returns to 5 reps if the 4-rep session this week is completed cleanly at pace. Week 3 moves to 57 km with the tempo block extended back toward 12 km and intervals returning to 6 reps. The original Week 3 target of 68 km is deferred by one week. If the revised sessions in Weeks 2 and 3 land at or near prescribed pace, the plan is back on track for a sub-3:15 marathon without any meaningful loss of fitness development.\"},\"net_load_delta\":-10,\"rationale\":\"Three consecutive sessions came in well below target: the tempo run drifted roughly 40 s/km slow, the interval session stopped at 3 of 6 reps with flat legs, and the long run was cut from 22 km to 14 km. That pattern across different session types points to accumulated fatigue rather than a single bad day. The week is restructured down from 58 km to 48 km. The interval session is rebuilt from 6 reps to 4, the tempo is trimmed from 12 km to 10 km with a shorter threshold block, and the long run is reduced from 22 km to 18 km. Tuesday's easy run stays unchanged. The physiological reason is straightforward: completing sessions at the right quality signal builds fitness. Grinding through volume at 40 s/km off pace does not. One reduced week preserves the training stimulus without compounding the fatigue. Week 2 steps back up to 52 km, and the full original loading resumes by Week 3 to 4. The 24-week timeline for sub-3:15 is intact.\",\"referral_category\":null}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "modelId": "\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"",
  "finishReason": "stop",
